trans-unit.source: Describes the width, height, and location of an integer rectangle.
XAML Attribute Usage
XAML Values
The x-coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
The y-coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
*Width*
The width of the rectangle.
*Height*
The height of the rectangle.
XAML Text Usage
You can also use whitespace instead of commas to delimit values.
Whitespace can also be used with a comma delimited value set.

Initializes a new instance of an <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> with the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref> and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref> coordinates and the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref> and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref> of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> instance which specifies the x-coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref> of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> instance which specifies the y-coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref> of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> instance which specifies the width of the rectangle.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref> of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> instance which specifies the height of the rectangle.
Gets the empty rectangle, a special value that represents a rectangle with no position or area.
This property is the same as calling the constructor using 0 for all parameter values.
XAML Attribute Usage
XAML Values
*property*
A property that accepts a <xref:System.Windows.Int32Rect> value.
An empty rectangle with no position or area.
Determines whether the specified rectangle is equal to this rectangle.
This operation tests for object equality.
The object to compare to the current rectangle.

**true** if *o* is an <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> and the same <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref> as this rectangle; otherwise, **false**.
Determines whether the specified rectangle is equal to this rectangle.
This operation tests for object equality.
The rectangle to compare to the current rectangle.

**true** if both rectangles have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref> as this rectangle; otherwise, **false**.
Determines whether the specified rectangles are equal.
This operation tests for object equality.
The first rectangle to compare.
The second rectangle to compare.

**true** if *int32Rect1* and *int32Rect2* have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref>; otherwise, **false**.

Creates a hash code from this rectangle's <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref> values.
This rectangle's hash code.

Gets a value that indicates whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref> and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref> properties of the <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> are greater than 0.
true if the and properties of the are greater than 0; otherwise, false.
Gets or sets the height of the rectangle.
The height of the rectangle.
The default value is 0.
Gets a value indicating whether the rectangle is empty.
**true** if the rectangle is empty; otherwise, **false**.
The default value is **true**.
Compares two rectangles for exact equality.
The equivalent method for this operator is <xref:System.Windows.Int32Rect.Equals%28System.Windows.Int32Rect%2CSystem.Windows.Int32Rect%29?displayProperty=fullName>
The first rectangle to compare.
The second rectangle to compare.

**true** if *int32Rect1* and *int32Rect2* have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref>; otherwise, **false**.
Compares two rectangles for inequality.
The equivalent method for this operator is the negation of <xref:System.Windows.Int32Rect.Equals%2A>.
The first rectangle to compare.
The second rectangle to compare.

**false** if *int32Rect1* and *int32Rect2* have the same <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Y"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Width"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect.Height"></xref>; otherwise, if all of these values are the same, then **true**.

Creates a string representation of this <xref href="System.Windows.Int32Rect"></xref> based on the supplied <xref href="System.IFormatProvider"></xref>.

If provider is `null`, the current culture is used.
